Basis for my arguement?  Let say I am pulling in PoV caves using proximity to pull mobs somewhat close together.  If the 2nd mob also agroes and I run back to camp without hitting the 2nd mob, it has an almost negligable amount of Hate for me...i.e. ANYTHING will pull it off me...heals, melee, debuffs, ect....<br>
If I'm meleeing the primary mob and no one picks up the 2nd, it will agro the first time I get healed.  Even if I AE Taunt immediately to get the 2nd mob back on me, it will still (and does) agro someone else again at the slightest provocation.<br>
If AE taunt gave me x number if &quot;extra&quot; hate, this wouldnt be the case, but it is.<br>
<br>
Note: the above situation is not theoretical, I spent 15 hours yesterday pulling PoV's outer caves for my group.  I used the AE taunt in the above situation not to lock the mob on me, but to buy a little time until it could be rooted by our shammy who was in charge of crowd control. <p>Veteran <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15858" target="top">Prytty Heartsmiter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
